1102:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c ****   */
1103:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c **** 
1104:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c **** /**
1105:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c ****   * @brief Send an amount of data in blocking mode.
1106:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c ****   * @note   When UART parity is not enabled (PCE = 0), and Word Length is configured to 9 bits (M1-
1107:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c ****   *         the sent data is handled as a set of u16. In this case, Size must indicate the number
1108:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c ****   *         of u16 provided through pData.
1109:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c ****   * @note When FIFO mode is enabled, writing a data in the TDR register adds one
1110:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart.c ****   *       data to the TXFIFO. Write operations to the TDR register are performed
